# Chromium Shell Browser Tabs — Public Façade (V3 simple_browser shell — M6)
#
# Thin re-export module so downstream code can write
# `use app.ui.chromium.browser_tabs.{TabManager, BrowserTab}` without
# having to know about the underlying `tab_manager.spl` implementation
# file. Mirrors the `event_bridge` / `backend` split used by M1/M2.
#
# Integration with `ChromiumApp` (multi-tab render loop, input
# fan-out, z-order compositing) is deliberately deferred to M7+; M6
# only requires that the tab data structure compile and support the
# create / count / switch / close operations.

use app.ui.chromium.tab_manager.{
    BrowserTab,
    TabManager,
    DEFAULT_TAB_WIDTH,
    DEFAULT_TAB_HEIGHT,
    DEFAULT_TAB_CLEAR
}

# Re-exports are declared in `__init__.spl` (the directory manifest).
# This file exists as a semantic façade: downstream code that wants
# the tab types explicitly from the chromium shell can write
# `use app.ui.chromium.browser_tabs.{TabManager, BrowserTab}` and the
# compiler resolves the symbols through the `use` bindings above.
